<p>
<seg id=1> Dear listeners, now let's see the development in China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=2> A few days ago, Chinese government took several persons with different political view into custody again, so to stop the gathering of Chinese Democratic Party members in Zhejiang and Shanghai. </seg>
<seg id=3> Please listen to the broadcasting of VOA Chinese department, reported by Qingyue. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to the news of Hong Kong headquartered Chinese Human Right and Democratic Movement Information Center, the public security persons of Hangzhou city took two members of Chinese Democratic Party, Zhu Zhengming and Mao Qinxiang, away from their home. </seg>
<seg id=5> No one knows where they are now. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before this, the police had arrested another four key persons of democratic movement who had close relations with Chinese Democratic Party, they were Yao Zhenxian, Li Guotao, Wu Yilong and Wang Rongqing respectively. </seg>
<seg id=7> According to Chinese Human Right and Democratic Movement Information Center, about twenty Chinese Democratic Party members from branches in Zhejiang and Shanghai originally planned to have their first meeting on Friday afternoon in a hotel in Hangzhou. </seg>
<seg id=8> Police took arrest operation aimed to this meeting. </seg>
<seg id=9> Meanwhile, the public security personnel in different places of Zhejiang province warned some other active democratic movement members not to go out of their homes, otherwise they would be arrested. </seg>
<seg id=10> Chinese government viewed this opposing faction party, Chinese Democratic Party, as an illegal organization, and ever arrested and interrogated tens of supporters and active members of this organization. </seg>
<seg id=11> But in most cases they were freed soon. </seg>
<seg id=12> Associated Press, Reuters, Ltd and Agency Francaise de Press reported this latest development issued by Chinese Human Right and Democratic Movement Information Center respectively. </seg>
</p>
